                                                            "nh2": "wix:image:\/\/v1\/f6985b_651a987d86bd4f41bb958ab25d47664f~mv2.jpg\/z6340990971278_52b490d29ab715b22efb6dcf17148c21.jpg#originWidth=1920&originHeight=2560",
                                                            "detail2": "<p class=\"font_8\"><br><\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\">Target audience: Anyone who enjoys fresh seafood at the market, with reasonable prices and the assurance of the freshest live fish, as customers can see and hear the quality firsthand.<\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\"><br><\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\">The display of goods is similar to traditional Vietnamese markets: wooden chairs and tables covered with plastic for easy cleaning, a simple style. However, hygiene and food safety are much better. With live fish, shrimp, and squid in clean tanks and tidy cooking areas, both tourists and locals feel comfortable enjoying the local cuisine.<\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\"><br><\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\">The seafood at the food stalls in the market is very diverse: cone shells, oysters, mackerel, and many more. Tourists are always curious to try, even if they're not hungry, as regional cuisine is an essential part of the local culture they want to experience.<\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\"><br><\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\">Some seafood, like lobsters and crabs, are also found in my hometown. While they are expensive in Vietnam, they are more affordable at the Busan Fish Market because the cold climate here is ideal for these types of seafood. On the other hand, tropical fruits are very expensive here and not as fresh as back home. This contrast highlights one of the reasons why traditional markets cater to tourists.<\/p>",
                                                            "nh3": "wix:image:\/\/v1\/f6985b_cba58a1996f44c3abc31f9c7448fdc1b~mv2.jpg\/z6340892036041_622f69728df014a8c44963a374271ecb.jpg#originWidth=1920&originHeight=2560",
                                                            "detail21": "<p class=\"font_8\"><strong>Image 1: Busan Fish Market - The Fish Market Building <\/strong>(<em>cre: Thanh Nien News<\/em>)<\/p>",
                                                            "description": "<p class=\"font_8\">When tourists visit any destination, they often want to learn about the local culture, history, standard of living, and customs. Traditional markets are an interesting place to explore the local culinary culture, eating habits, income levels, and specialties.<\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\">During my trip to South Korea in November 2016, as a tourist, I was very excited to visit the Busan Fish Market. So, what did I discover when I visited this market in Korea?<\/p>",
                                                            "_id": "2b40a4b0-aadd-49d5-ac53-704b8337c87c",
