                                                            "title11": "<h5 class=\"font_5\"><strong>Depending on who goes to the market?<\/strong><\/h5>",
                                                            "detail212": "<p class=\"font_8\"><strong>Depending on the shopper's income and consumer behaviour<\/strong><\/p>",
                                                            "nh1": "wix:image:\/\/v1\/f6985b_6048710ecd484e849d10d9f82640a205~mv2.jpg\/ch%E1%BB%A3.jpg#originWidth=665&originHeight=444",
                                                            "detail": "<p class=\"font_8\">The choice of where to shop depends on the type of product being purchased. When spending significant amounts of money, buyers want to ensure they are making the right decision. Shopping is not just about necessity; it is also a leisure activity, often enjoyed with family or friends.<\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\"><br><\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\">Residents of Ninh Sim Commune prefer to shop at Dinh Market (Ninh Hoa) for Tet holiday preparations. People in Ninh Hoa Town often visit Dam Market or Xom Moi Market in Nha Trang. Nha Trang residents sometimes travel to Ho Chi Minh City to shop at Ben Thanh Market or An Dong Market.<\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\"><br><\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\">Vietnamese people shopping in Seoul or Bangkok isn’t always about product availability or lower prices. It’s often due to the belief that foreign goods are superior, which reflects the saying, “A prophet is not honored in his own country.”<\/p>",
                                                            "detail3": "<p class=\"font_8\">People with higher incomes often shop at supermarkets for convenience, buying items that last for several days. The quality of goods is better controlled in supermarkets. This group makes up about 10% of the population and prefers premium quality products, showing less interest in more affordable options. They like organic, traceable vegetables and high-end branded goods.<\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\"><br><\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\">Meanwhile, people with lower incomes tend to go to the market. They shop for their basic daily needs, with fresh food like meat, fish, vegetables, and fruits being the main items. They visit the market daily because it offers flexible prices, is more affordable, and provides fresher products.<\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\"><br><\/p>\n<p class=\"font_8\">Due to the hot and humid climate with only two seasons—rainy and dry—fresh food is readily available in Vietnam. As a result, people do not typically buy frozen food to store at home but prefer to purchase fresh food daily.<\/p>",
